🔧 Instruction for Claude Code: Portfolio Website Build
Goal

Create a personal portfolio website for Abdullah Baleid, based on the attached CV, that blends:

Follow.art’s minimal, content-first elegance

LandoNorris.com’s scroll-driven, cinematic storytelling

The result should feel premium, modern, and intentional, not like a generic student portfolio.

🧠 Overall UX Concept

Treat the website as a guided narrative, not a list of sections.

Use scroll as the main interaction driver (like landonorris.com).

Use clean layouts, whitespace, and restrained UI (like follow.art).

Prioritize clarity, confidence, and credibility over visual noise.

🎨 Visual Language & Style
Global Style

Dark mode default with subtle accent color (soft neon green / electric blue).

Large typography with strong hierarchy.

Minimal UI chrome (no heavy borders, no boxed layouts).

Smooth easing animations (no aggressive motion).

Motion Principles

Subtle fades, vertical reveals, and parallax for content sections.

Scroll-triggered transitions between major sections.

Hover effects that reveal information, not distract.

